wfDs1E1ModuleTable.name: wfDs1E1ModuleTable
wfDs1E1ModuleTable.description: This file describes the MIBS for managing the Multichannel T1 and E1 link modules. DS1E1 MOD record - Contains DS1E1 module Configuration parameters

wfDs1E1ModuleEntry.name: wfDs1E1ModuleEntry
wfDs1E1ModuleEntry.description: An entry in the DS1E1 Base table

wfDs1E1ModuleSlot.name: wfDs1E1ModuleSlot
wfDs1E1ModuleSlot.description: Instance ID slot, filled in by driver

wfDs1E1ModuleModule.name: wfDs1E1ModuleModule
wfDs1E1ModuleModule.description: Instance ID slot, filled in by driver

wfDs1E1ModulePrimaryClock.name: wfDs1E1ModulePrimaryClock
wfDs1E1ModulePrimaryClock.description: Specifies the primary source for transmit timing. Both ports use the same transmit timing source. The options for timing source are internal timing source, loop timing from either port and an external timing source.

wfDs1E1ModuleSecondaryClock.name: wfDs1E1ModuleSecondaryClock
wfDs1E1ModuleSecondaryClock.description: Specifies the secondary source for transmit timing. During normal operation transmit timing is derived from the primary timing source. If the primary timing source fails, the software switches to secondary timing source.

wfDs1E1ModuleCurrentClock.name: wfDs1E1ModuleCurrentClock
wfDs1E1ModuleCurrentClock.description: Indicates the clock source currently in use

wfDs1E1ModuleExtClockOperational.name: wfDs1E1ModuleExtClockOperational
wfDs1E1ModuleExtClockOperational.description: Indicates whether the External clock is operational

wfDs1E1ModuleLoop1ClockOperational.name: wfDs1E1ModuleLoop1ClockOperational
wfDs1E1ModuleLoop1ClockOperational.description: Indicates whether the timing source from port 1 is operational

wfDs1E1ModuleLoop2ClockOperational.name: wfDs1E1ModuleLoop2ClockOperational
wfDs1E1ModuleLoop2ClockOperational.description: Indicates whether the timing source from port 2 is operational

wfDs1E1ModuleLoop3ClockOperational.name: wfDs1E1ModuleLoop3ClockOperational
wfDs1E1ModuleLoop3ClockOperational.description: Indicates whether the timing source from port 3 is operational

wfDs1E1ModuleLoop4ClockOperational.name: wfDs1E1ModuleLoop4ClockOperational
wfDs1E1ModuleLoop4ClockOperational.description: Indicates whether the timing source from port 4 is operational

wfDs1E1ModuleCfgTxBufferUseCredits.name: wfDs1E1ModuleCfgTxBufferUseCredits
wfDs1E1ModuleCfgTxBufferUseCredits.description: Configured Transmit Buffer Credits. Values other than zero over-ride the router selected values. A value of zero has a special meaning. Zero causes router based default values to be used. All values are accepted. Care should be taken not to set this to a value which is much greater than the default. The default can be read out of the wfDs1E1ModuleTxBufferUseCredits attribute when the router is running with this attribute set to zero. Sets to this attribute may take up to one minute to take effect.

wfDs1E1ModuleCfgRxBufferUseCredits.name: wfDs1E1ModuleCfgRxBufferUseCredits
wfDs1E1ModuleCfgRxBufferUseCredits.description: Configured Receive Buffer Credits. Values other than zero over-ride the router selected values. A value of zero has a special meaning. Zero cuases router based default values to be used. Values larger than the compiled ring size are truncated to the compiled ring size. Sets to this attribute may take up to one minute to take effect.

wfDs1E1ModuleTxBufferUseCredits.name: wfDs1E1ModuleTxBufferUseCredits
wfDs1E1ModuleTxBufferUseCredits.description: Current Transmit Buffers available for use by module

wfDs1E1ModuleRxBufferUseCredits.name: wfDs1E1ModuleRxBufferUseCredits
wfDs1E1ModuleRxBufferUseCredits.description: Current Receive Buffers available for use by module

wfDs1E1PortMapTable.name: wfDs1E1PortMapTable
wfDs1E1PortMapTable.description: DS1E1 port map record - Used by the driver to identify the LineNumber for the Port. The only table indexed by slot.connector. Its purpose is to map slot.connector to a PortLineNumber.

wfDs1E1PortMapEntry.name: wfDs1E1PortMapEntry
wfDs1E1PortMapEntry.description: An entry in the DS1E1 port table

wfDs1E1PortMapSlot.name: wfDs1E1PortMapSlot
wfDs1E1PortMapSlot.description: Instance ID Slot, filled in by driver

wfDs1E1PortMapConnector.name: wfDs1E1PortMapConnector
wfDs1E1PortMapConnector.description: Instance ID Connector, filled in by driver

wfDs1E1PortMapLineNumber.name: wfDs1E1PortMapLineNumber
wfDs1E1PortMapLineNumber.description: LineNumber off of which all other MIB instances are indexed.

wfDs1E1PortMapDslId.name: wfDs1E1PortMapDslId
wfDs1E1PortMapDslId.description: When this T1/E1 interface is configured for Primary Rate ISDN (PRI) this attribute provides the ID of this Digital Subscriber Loop (DSL) interface. Each T1 or E1 PRI interface on a particular slot is assigned a unique DSL ID.

wfDs1E1PortTable.name: wfDs1E1PortTable
wfDs1E1PortTable.description: DS1E1 port record - Contains MUNICH32 Configuration parameters

wfDs1E1PortEntry.name: wfDs1E1PortEntry
wfDs1E1PortEntry.description: An entry in the DS1E1 port table

wfDs1E1PortLineNumber.name: wfDs1E1PortLineNumber
wfDs1E1PortLineNumber.description: LineNumber for this port. This value is assigned at configuration time and uniquely identifies this interface. This LineNumber not equal to any of the LineNumbers assigned to the LogicalLines configured through this Port.

wfDs1E1PortMtu.name: wfDs1E1PortMtu
wfDs1E1PortMtu.description: MTU parameter. Obsoleted, it is no longer referenced.

wfDs1E1PortSignalLevel.name: wfDs1E1PortSignalLevel
wfDs1E1PortSignalLevel.description: Specifies T1 transmit power level, in terms of DB. They translate into cable length as follows: 0.0dB -> 0-133 ft 0.5dB -> 133-266 ft 0.8dB -> 266-399 ft 1.1dB -> 399-533 ft 1.5dB -> 533-655 ft

wfDs1E1PortSetupAlarmThreshold.name: wfDs1E1PortSetupAlarmThreshold
wfDs1E1PortSetupAlarmThreshold.description: Specifies setup time for performance failure conditions, in seconds. When a performance defect is present for greater than the time specified by this parameter a performance failure is registered and a message is logged.

wfDs1E1PortClearAlarmThreshold.name: wfDs1E1PortClearAlarmThreshold
wfDs1E1PortClearAlarmThreshold.description: Specifies clear time for performance failure conditions, in seconds. When a performance failure condition has been cleared for greater than the time specified by this parameter then the failure cleared condition is registered and a message is logged.

wfDs1E1PortFdlTargetHdlcAddress.name: wfDs1E1PortFdlTargetHdlcAddress
wfDs1E1PortFdlTargetHdlcAddress.description: Selects between the two FDL target address modes. This determines whether the near-end FDL will respond to HDLC address AZ or BY in the FDL messages received from the far-end.

wfDs1E1PortAcceptLoopbackRequest.name: wfDs1E1PortAcceptLoopbackRequest
wfDs1E1PortAcceptLoopbackRequest.description: The DS1E1 link module is capable of detecting loop up and loop down codes received from the far end. This parameter enables and disables loop up/down code detection circuitry. If enabled, this interface will accept and comply with a request to go into loopback mode from a far end device.

wfDs1E1PortLoopbackState.name: wfDs1E1PortLoopbackState
wfDs1E1PortLoopbackState.description: Indicates the current loopback state of this interface. The interface can be in one the following states: Payload Loopback Line Loopback no loopback Payload or Line loopback modes can be initiated by either of two methods: Manager requested Loopback (MGRREQPAYLOADLOOP or MGRREQLINELOOP) is initiated by the Manager of this device. Network requested Loopback (NETREQPAYLOADLOOP or NETREQLINELOOP) is initiated by this interface receiving an in-band request on the network from the far end device.

wfDs1E1PortBertMode.name: wfDs1E1PortBertMode
wfDs1E1PortBertMode.description: An option to generate and analyze specific test patterns is provided in BERT mode of operation. Only one port can be in BERT mode at a time. This attribute selects normal or BERT mode of operation

wfDs1E1PortBertTestPattern.name: wfDs1E1PortBertTestPattern
wfDs1E1PortBertTestPattern.description: When a port is in BERT mode, it is capable of generating a set of known patterns. This paramater selects between those patterns

wfDs1E1PortBertSendAlarm.name: wfDs1E1PortBertSendAlarm
wfDs1E1PortBertSendAlarm.description: Specifies a Alarm Indication Signal (AIS) (Blue Alarm) or yellow alarm to be transmitted while in BERT mode.

wfDs1E1PortInternationalBit.name: wfDs1E1PortInternationalBit
wfDs1E1PortInternationalBit.description: Specifies if the International bit should be set in the E1 frame

wfDs1E1PortLineApplication.name: wfDs1E1PortLineApplication
wfDs1E1PortLineApplication.description: Specifies the application that the LogicalLines of this Port will provide. NONPRI indicates that all of the LogicalLines will have a permanent Cct number and will not be used to dial to varying destinations. PRI indicates that some or all of the ds0s of this port will be used for switched Ccts using ISDN. MIXED indicates that some of the ds0s are being used for switched Ccts using ISDN and some are being used for non PRI permanent connections for other applications such as leased lines or Frame Relay.

wfDs1E1PortLoggingEnableMask.name: wfDs1E1PortLoggingEnableMask
wfDs1E1PortLoggingEnableMask.description: Specifies which catagories of extended event log messages are enabled for logging. Current bit definitions are: bit 31 bit 0 +--------------------------------+ | | +--------------------------------+ bit0 ISDN PRI debug messages bit1-31 reserved

wfDs1E1PortSendPrmCrAddressBit.name: wfDs1E1PortSendPrmCrAddressBit
wfDs1E1PortSendPrmCrAddressBit.description: Specifies the Performance message as originating from either a Carrier or Customer Installation (CI). As the performance message is sent out the FDL, the PRM Opening Address C/R bit is either set (Carrier) or cleared (CI). This feature is only supported by the QMCT1.

wfDs1E1PortAcceptPrmCrAddressBit.name: wfDs1E1PortAcceptPrmCrAddressBit
wfDs1E1PortAcceptPrmCrAddressBit.description: Accepts only Performance messages originating from either a Carrier or Customer Installation (CI), as determined below. The PRM Opening Address C/R bit is read upon receiving a performance message. If the Performance message does not originate from the expected source, it is discarded. This feature is only supported by the QMCT1.

wfDs1E1PortLineImpedanceOption.name: wfDs1E1PortLineImpedanceOption
wfDs1E1PortLineImpedanceOption.description: Supports user selectible Line Impedance option for ASN MCE1 Net Modules.

wfDs1E1PortFdlLoopInterframeFill.name: wfDs1E1PortFdlLoopInterframeFill
wfDs1E1PortFdlLoopInterframeFill.description: Enables the Loop Retention Interframe Time Fill for the FDL after sending Loop Up Code. Also enables the detection of the Loop Retention Code when placed into Line or Payload loopback by the remote end.

wfDs1E1PortRelayCtrl.name: wfDs1E1PortRelayCtrl
wfDs1E1PortRelayCtrl.description: The Relay on the QMCT1 will always be placed into loopback for the following conditions: 1. Power Up 2. Reboot 3. Hardware Reset Button 4. System CRASH However, when altering QMCT1 Port or Module MIBs' attributes with a restart characteristic, the state of the Relay will be controlled by this MIB attribute. When set to loop (1), the Relay will go into loopback as the Port/Module is re-initialized. The Relay will come out of loopback as the Port/Module re-initialization is complete. When set to noLoop (2), the Relay will remain in its present state as the Port/Module is re-initialized.

wfDs1E1PortRelayStatus.name: wfDs1E1PortRelayStatus
wfDs1E1PortRelayStatus.description: This attribute indicates the current state of the Relay on the QMCT1. When set to loop (1), the Relay is currently looping data from the Rx path onto the Tx path. When set to noLoop (2), the Rx path and Tx path are connected to the Framer. Note that the Framer may be placed into loopback without affecting this attribute.

wfDs1E1PortPrimaryClockSource.name: wfDs1E1PortPrimaryClockSource
wfDs1E1PortPrimaryClockSource.description: Selects the Primary source of the Tx Clock for the DS1/E1 interface

wfDs1E1PortSecondaryClockSource.name: wfDs1E1PortSecondaryClockSource
wfDs1E1PortSecondaryClockSource.description: Selects the Secondary source of the Tx Clock for the DS1/E1 interface

wfDs1E1PortCurrentClock.name: wfDs1E1PortCurrentClock
wfDs1E1PortCurrentClock.description: Indicates the clock source currently in use by the DS1

wfDs1E1PortExtClockOperational.name: wfDs1E1PortExtClockOperational
wfDs1E1PortExtClockOperational.description: Indicates whether the External clock is operational

wfDs1E1PortTransmitWaveform.name: wfDs1E1PortTransmitWaveform
wfDs1E1PortTransmitWaveform.description: Specifies T1 transmit waveform settings. Legal values are: long haul (LBO 0.0dB) long haul (LBO 7.5dB) long haul (LBO 15.0dB) long haul (LBO 22.5dB) short haul (0-110 ft) short haul (110-220 ft) short haul (220-330 ft) short haul (330-440 ft) short haul (440-550 ft) short haul (550-660 ft) Note that this attribute is not supported by all T1 interfaces. For those interfaces that DO NOT support this attribute, the wfDs1E1PortSignalLevel attribute is used instead.

wfDs1E1ConfigTable.name: wfDs1E1ConfigTable
wfDs1E1ConfigTable.description: DS1E1 Configuration Table. This is a copy of the dsx1ConfigTable found in RFC1406. The table is indexed with PortLineNumber instead of ifIndex, however.

wfDs1E1ConfigEntry.name: wfDs1E1ConfigEntry
wfDs1E1ConfigEntry.description: An entry in the DS1E1 config table

wfDs1E1ConfigPortLineNumber.name: wfDs1E1ConfigPortLineNumber
wfDs1E1ConfigPortLineNumber.description: The index ID for this record. It is the line number assigned to a port in the wfDs1E1PortMapEntry for a port.connector pair. Its channel field should be 0.

wfDs1E1ConfigIfIndex.name: wfDs1E1ConfigIfIndex
wfDs1E1ConfigIfIndex.description: Currently this is the sames as wfDs1E1LinePortIndex

wfDs1E1ConfigTimeElapsed.name: wfDs1E1ConfigTimeElapsed
wfDs1E1ConfigTimeElapsed.description: The number of seconds that have elapsed since the beginning of the current error-measurement period. Only relevant when the wfDs1E1ConfigLineType is ESF and the wfDs1E1ConfigFdl is AT&T 54016.

wfDs1E1ConfigValidIntervals.name: wfDs1E1ConfigValidIntervals
wfDs1E1ConfigValidIntervals.description: The number of previous intervals for which valid data was collected. The value will be 96 unless the interface was brought on-line within the last 24 hours, in which case the value will be the number of complete 15 minute intervals the since interface has been online. Only relevant when the wfDs1E1ConfigLineType is ESF and the wfDs1E1ConfigFdl is AT&T 54016.

wfDs1E1ConfigLineType.name: wfDs1E1ConfigLineType
wfDs1E1ConfigLineType.description: This attribute is used to configure the line framing type to match the carrier's framing. SF and ESF are T1 framing types and the main differences between the two are the number of frames in a superframe and the use of the f-bit. The E1, E1CRC, E1MF, and E1CRCMF are used for E1 lines.

wfDs1E1ConfigLineCoding.name: wfDs1E1ConfigLineCoding
wfDs1E1ConfigLineCoding.description: This variable describes the variety of Zero Code Suppression used on the link, which in turn affects a number of its characteristics. It should be set to match the carrier. AMI (alternate mark inversion) refers to a mode wherein no zero code suppression is present and the line encoding does not solve the problem directly. In this application, the higher layer must provide data which meets or exceeds the pulse density requirements, such as inverting HDLC data. This could be used for T1 or E1 lines. B8ZS refers to the use of a specified pattern of normal bits and bipolar violations which are used to replace a sequence of eight zero bits. This can be used on T1 lines while HDB3 provides similar functionality for E1 links.

wfDs1E1ConfigSendCode.name: wfDs1E1ConfigSendCode
wfDs1E1ConfigSendCode.description: This variable is currently read-only and it indicates what type of code is being sent across the DS1 interface by the device. The values mean: SENDNOCODE - sending looped or normal data SENDLINECODE - sending a request for a line loopback SENDPAYLOADCODE - sending a request for a payload loopback SENDRESETCODE - sending a loopback termination request SENDQRS - sending a Quasi-Random Signal (QRS) test pattern SEND511PATTERN - sending a 511 bit fixed test pattern SEND3IN24PATTERN - sending a fixed test pattern of 3 bits set in 24 SENDOTHERTESTPATTERN - sending a test pattern other than those described by this object

wfDs1E1ConfigCircuitIdentifier.name: wfDs1E1ConfigCircuitIdentifier
wfDs1E1ConfigCircuitIdentifier.description: This attribute is not used and appears here as a place holder only. If it was implemented then it would contain the transmission vendor's circuit identifier, for the purpose of facilitating troubleshooting.

wfDs1E1ConfigLoopbackConfig.name: wfDs1E1ConfigLoopbackConfig
wfDs1E1ConfigLoopbackConfig.description: This variable represents the loopback configuration of the DS1 interface. The value NOLOOP indicates the port is not in loopback. The value PAYLOADLOOP indicates the port is in payload loopback which means that data is looped back after it goes through the framer. The value LINELOOP indicates the port is in line loopback which means that data is looped back before the framer.

wfDs1E1ConfigLineStatus.name: wfDs1E1ConfigLineStatus
wfDs1E1ConfigLineStatus.description: This variable is a bit-map which indicates the Line Status of the interface. It contains loopback, failure, received 'alarm' and transmitted 'alarm' information. The bit definition as as follows with bit #0 being the LSB. bit 0 NOALARM - No alarm present, set only when none of the other bits are. 1 RCVFARENDLOF - Far end LOF (a.k.a., Yellow Alarm) 2 XMTFARENDLOF - Near end sending LOF Indication 3 RCVAIS - Far end sending AIS 4 XMTAIS - Near end sending AIS 5 LOSSOFFRAME - Near end LOF (a.k.a., Red Alarm) 6 LOSSOFSIGNAL - Near end Loss Of Signal 7 LOOPBACKSTATE - Near end is looped 8 T16AIS - E1 only, TS16 AIS 9 RCVFARENDLOMF - E1 only, Far End Sending TS16 LOMF 10 XMTFARENDLOMF - E1 only, Near End Sending TS16 LOMF 11 RCVTESTCODE - Near End detects a test code 12 OTHERFAILURE - any line status not defined here'

wfDs1E1ConfigSignalMode.name: wfDs1E1ConfigSignalMode
wfDs1E1ConfigSignalMode.description: This attribute is not implemented and exists here only as a place holder.

wfDs1E1ConfigTransmitClockSource.name: wfDs1E1ConfigTransmitClockSource
wfDs1E1ConfigTransmitClockSource.description: The source of Tranmit Clock. LOOPTIMING indicates that the recovered receive clock is used as the transmit clock. LOCALTIMING indicates that a local clock source is used. Either the internal clock or the external clock through the extra connector on the board. THROUGHTIMING indicates that recovered receive clock from another interface is used as the transmit clock.

wfDs1E1ConfigFdl.name: wfDs1E1ConfigFdl
wfDs1E1ConfigFdl.description: This attribute is used to configure the type facilities data link (FDL). The ANSI403 configures the port to use the FDL exchange described in the ANSI T1 403 specification. ATT54016 is used to configure the port for the for the FDL exchange listed in the AT&T 54016 document. NONE is used when no FDL is desired. The FDL can only be used when the line type is ESF.

wfDs1E1ActionTable.name: wfDs1E1ActionTable
wfDs1E1ActionTable.description: DS1E1 configuration Action record - Contains MUNICH32 and Framer write only Configuration parameters

wfDs1E1ActionEntry.name: wfDs1E1ActionEntry
wfDs1E1ActionEntry.description: An entry in the DS1E1 Config table

wfDs1E1ActionPortLineNumber.name: wfDs1E1ActionPortLineNumber
wfDs1E1ActionPortLineNumber.description: Instance ID LineNumber, filled in by driver

wfDs1E1ActionBertErrorInsert.name: wfDs1E1ActionBertErrorInsert
wfDs1E1ActionBertErrorInsert.description: Indicates that an error be injected into the transmitted data stream while in BERT mode.

wfDs1E1ActionSendLoopCode.name: wfDs1E1ActionSendLoopCode
wfDs1E1ActionSendLoopCode.description: Selects a Loop Up/Down code to be sent to the remote end

wfDs1E1ActionSendFdlLoopbackCode.name: wfDs1E1ActionSendFdlLoopbackCode
wfDs1E1ActionSendFdlLoopbackCode.description: Selects an FDL code to be sent to the remote end.

wfDs1E1ActionSendLoopUpFractionalCode.name: wfDs1E1ActionSendLoopUpFractionalCode
wfDs1E1ActionSendLoopUpFractionalCode.description: Selects Fractional Loop Up code to be sent to the remote end. Value passed through this attribute is the Logical Line number (1 through 24). This feature is only supported by the QMCT1.

wfDs1E1ActionSendLoopDownFractionalCode.name: wfDs1E1ActionSendLoopDownFractionalCode
wfDs1E1ActionSendLoopDownFractionalCode.description: Selects Fractional Loop Down code to be sent to the remote end. Value passed through this attribute is the Logical Line number (1 through 24). This feature is only supported by the QMCT1.

wfDs1E1ActionClearFractionalLoopState.name: wfDs1E1ActionClearFractionalLoopState
wfDs1E1ActionClearFractionalLoopState.description: Removes any Logical Line left in hardware Fractional T1 loopback state. The Logical Line number is passed as an argument. This feature is only supported by the QMCT1.

wfDs1E1ActionClearFdlStats.name: wfDs1E1ActionClearFdlStats
wfDs1E1ActionClearFdlStats.description: Clears this port's FDL Statistics. This feature is only supported by the QMCT1.

wfDs1E1ActionClearCurrentStats.name: wfDs1E1ActionClearCurrentStats
wfDs1E1ActionClearCurrentStats.description: Clears this port's Current 15 minute Statistics.

wfDs1E1ActionClearFarEndCurrentStats.name: wfDs1E1ActionClearFarEndCurrentStats
wfDs1E1ActionClearFarEndCurrentStats.description: Clears this port's Far End, Current 15 minute Statistics.

wfDs1E1ActionClearDayCurrentStats.name: wfDs1E1ActionClearDayCurrentStats
wfDs1E1ActionClearDayCurrentStats.description: Clears this port's Current Day Statistics.

wfDs1E1ActionClearFarEndDayCurrentStats.name: wfDs1E1ActionClearFarEndDayCurrentStats
wfDs1E1ActionClearFarEndDayCurrentStats.description: Clears this port's Far End, Current Day Statistics.

wfDs1E1ActionClearIntervalStats.name: wfDs1E1ActionClearIntervalStats
wfDs1E1ActionClearIntervalStats.description: Clears All Interval Statistics (15 minute and day) of this port.

wfDs1E1ActionClearFarEndIntervalStats.name: wfDs1E1ActionClearFarEndIntervalStats
wfDs1E1ActionClearFarEndIntervalStats.description: Clears All Far End Interval Statistics (15 minute and day) of this port.

wfLogicalLineTable.name: wfLogicalLineTable
wfLogicalLineTable.description: LogicalLine record - Contains configuration parameters and statistics for MUNICH32 which are LogicalLine specific.

wfLogicalLineEntry.name: wfLogicalLineEntry
wfLogicalLineEntry.description: An entry in the LOGICAL_LINE table

wfLogicalLinePortLineNumber.name: wfLogicalLinePortLineNumber
wfLogicalLinePortLineNumber.description: Instance ID PortLineNumber, filled in by driver

wfLogicalLineIndex.name: wfLogicalLineIndex
wfLogicalLineIndex.description: Index for this line instance, filled in by driver. The index corresponds to the position of the circuit, from 1 to 31, on the port.

wfLogicalLineCct.name: wfLogicalLineCct
wfLogicalLineCct.description: Circuit number for this line instance

wfLogicalLineLineNumber.name: wfLogicalLineLineNumber
wfLogicalLineLineNumber.description: LineNumber for this logical line instance. This is the same line number contained in the PORT_TABLE with the channel field nonzero.

wfLogicalLineBofl.name: wfLogicalLineBofl
wfLogicalLineBofl.description: Selects Breath of Life (BOFL) parameter. If selected, a BOFL packet is sent out on the wire as often as specifies by the wfLogicalLineBoflTmo parameter

wfLogicalLineBoflTmo.name: wfLogicalLineBoflTmo
wfLogicalLineBoflTmo.description: Indicates the time-period between BOFL packets

wfLogicalLineFractionalLoopback.name: wfLogicalLineFractionalLoopback
wfLogicalLineFractionalLoopback.description: Any Logical Line on this T1/E1 port is capable of being put into loopback, i.e. data coming into that circuit from the wire is mirrorred back onto the wire. This parameter enables or disables this loopback feature on any circuit.

wfLogicalLineTimeSlotAssignment.name: wfLogicalLineTimeSlotAssignment
wfLogicalLineTimeSlotAssignment.description: Lists the time-slots which constitute this channel. Read only attribute that contains a list of time-slots from 1 to 31 used by the channel

wfLogicalLineMtu.name: wfLogicalLineMtu
wfLogicalLineMtu.description: Contains the largest frame size that can be received by the logical line. Anything larger than the MTU will be discarded. In all cases except when the wfLogicalLineWanProtocol is LAPB, this value will be the same as wfLogicalLineCfgMtu. In the LAPB case it will be twice wfLogicalLineCfgMtu with a maximum of 4608.

wfLogicalLineMadr.name: wfLogicalLineMadr
wfLogicalLineMadr.description: Line MAC address, fixed - line driver fills in from the 48 bit address stored in the serial number prom.

wfLogicalLineWanProtocol.name: wfLogicalLineWanProtocol
wfLogicalLineWanProtocol.description: WAN protocol selection is provided via this parameter. The supported protocols can be selected per circuit.

wfLogicalLineHdlcService.name: wfLogicalLineHdlcService
wfLogicalLineHdlcService.description: HDLC Service type for this line. Transparent is raw HDLC mode, LLC1 will prefix the HDLC address and control fields to the frame.

wfLogicalLineLocalHdlcAddress.name: wfLogicalLineLocalHdlcAddress
wfLogicalLineLocalHdlcAddress.description: This attribute is only used if the Wan protocol is Wellfleet Standard Proprietary Point to Point. This attribute is unused for other Wan protocols. The local HDLC address can take on values between 1 and 7. The default is 7. 1 is refered to as DCE. 3 is refered to DTE. All others are refered to as EXPLICIT. EXPLICIT indicates that the user has explicitely selected the address.

wfLogicalLineRemoteHdlcAddress.name: wfLogicalLineRemoteHdlcAddress
wfLogicalLineRemoteHdlcAddress.description: This attribute is only used if the Wan protocol is Wellfleet Standard Proprietary Point to Point. This attribute is unused for other Wan protocols. The remote HDLC address can take on values between 1 and 7. The default is 7. 1 is refered to as DCE. 3 is refered to DTE. All others are refered to as EXPLICIT. EXPLICIT indicates that the user has explicitely selected the address.

wfLogicalLineRateAdaption.name: wfLogicalLineRateAdaption
wfLogicalLineRateAdaption.description: Determines the number of bits and their bit positions within the time-slot. 64k selection uses all 8 bits in the time-slot. The two 56k selections use 7 of the 8 bits in the time-slot. 56k_MSB does not use the most significant bit and 56k_LSB does not use the least significant bit in the time-slot. If the logical line is configured for DS0-A operation, rate adaptions of 9.6 Kbps and 19.2 Kbps may be configured.

wfLogicalLineIFTF.name: wfLogicalLineIFTF
wfLogicalLineIFTF.description: Determines the Interframe time fill character to be transmitted by the MUNICH. In case of IFTF_FLAGS, 0x7E is sent and in case of IFTF_IDLES 0xff is sent as the interframe timefill characters.

wfLogicalLineCRCSize.name: wfLogicalLineCRCSize
wfLogicalLineCRCSize.description: Determines the CRC Size. When CRC32 is selected a 32 bit CRC is appended to the frame being transmitted and a 32 bit CRC check is performed on the received frame. When CRC16 is selected, a 16 bit CRC is appended to the transmitted frame and a 16 bit CRC is performed. on the received frame.

wfLogicalLineRxOctets.name: wfLogicalLineRxOctets
wfLogicalLineRxOctets.description: Number of octets received without error

wfLogicalLineRxFrames.name: wfLogicalLineRxFrames
wfLogicalLineRxFrames.description: Number of frames received without error

wfLogicalLineTxOctets.name: wfLogicalLineTxOctets
wfLogicalLineTxOctets.description: Number of octets transmitted without error

wfLogicalLineTxFrames.name: wfLogicalLineTxFrames
wfLogicalLineTxFrames.description: Number of frames transmitted without error

wfLogicalLineLackRxResources.name: wfLogicalLineLackRxResources

wfLogicalLineRemoteLpbkDetection.description: This attribute enables Remote Loopback Detection. wfLogicalLineRxIdles.name: wfLogicalLineRxIdles
wfLogicalLineRxIdles.description: Number of received frames followed by ShortFrame errors reported by the hardware. ShortFrame errors imediately after received frames actually indicates an Idle (all 1s) interframe time fill. One ShortFrame is allowed per received frame without incrementing wfLogicalLineRxErrors or wfLogicalLineRxShortFrames. Additional ShortFrames will not increment wfLogicalLineRxIdles but will increment both wfLogicalLineRxErrors and wfLogicalLineRxShortFrames.

wfLogicalLineRole.name: wfLogicalLineRole
wfLogicalLineRole.description: Specifies the role of this Logical Line. This attribute directs the Logical Line to be either a normal permanent synchronous connection, a Primary Rate ISDN 'D' channel or a Primary Rate ISDN 'B' channel.

wfLogicalLineActiveCct.description: Active CCT number for this LogicalLine. Used in ISDN PRI to indicate the CCT of the current call in progress.

wfLogicalLineActualRateAdaption.name: wfLogicalLineActualRateAdaption
wfLogicalLineActualRateAdaption.description: Indicates the current Rate Adaption in use. This may differ from the configured Rate Adaption in ISDN PRI applications. This attribute indicates the number of bits and their bit positions within the time-slot. 64k selection uses all 8 bits in the time-slot. The two 56k selections use 7 of the 8 bits in the time-slot. 56k_MSB does not use the most significant bit and 56k_LSB does not use the least significant bit in the time-slot. If the logical line is configured for DS0-A operation, rate adaptions of 9.6 Kbps and 19.2 Kbps may be configured.
